global warming. The book presents all the players in the most pressing challenge facing society today, from the massive fossil fuel lobby to the enlightened corporations that are joining the movement to "go green." Musil thoroughly explains the tremendous potential of renewable energy sources-wind, solar, and biofuel-and the startling conclusions of experts who say society can do away entirely with fossil fuels. He tells readers about the engaged politicians, activists, religious groups, and students who are already working together against climate change. But the future depends, Musil insists, on what changes ordinary citizens make. Through personal choices and political engagement, he shows how readers can cut carbon emissions and create green communities where they live. With practical and realistic solutions, Hope for a Heated Planet inspires readers to be accountable and enables them to usher in an age of sustainability for future generations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aCarbon dioxidexPhysiological effect. 0aCarbon dioxide-Physiological effect. 0aClimatic changeszUnited States. 0aClimatic changes-United States. 0aGlobal warmingxHealth aspects. 0aGlobal warming-Health aspects. 0aGlobal warming. 0aGreen movement. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aHope for a Heated Planet, global warming, grassroots efforts, Robert K. Musil, Nobel Peace Prize-winning organization, Physicians for Social Responsibility, climate movement, economy, public health, environmentalism, renewable energy, fossil fuel lobby, green corporations, wind energy, solar energy, biofuel, political activism, societal change, carbon emissions reduction, green communities, sustainability, environmental advocacy, climate solutions, climate justice, personal responsibility, political engagement, social change, environmental awareness, 